Why Choose NTTF?

NTTF offers a transformative learning environment that goes beyond textbooks. We focus on hands-on projects and industry-standard tools, preparing you with the practical skills employers seek.

Thrive in the Real World

NTTF’s learning environment breaks the mold, offering a dynamic blend of practical training and theoretical knowledge. We believe in equipping you for the real world, so a significant 65% of your learning experience will be dedicated to hands-on training.

Industry Connections

Our unrivaled network of industry partners provides unparalleled access to internships, mentorships, and job opportunities. Get real-world experience and build valuable connections before you graduate.

Campus Placements

NTTF boasts a strong track record of student success. We conduct on-campus placement drives, connecting you with top MNCs and reputable firms. Many of our graduates secure positions at leading MNCs and reputable firms.

Wide Recognitions

NTTF’s diplomas and programs are recognized by NCVET, MSDE, Govt. if India at Level 4.5, signifying high-quality education that meets industry standards. This recognition can potentially open doors to jobs and higher education.

Transformative Learning Environment

Extensive Industry Partnerships

FAQs

What is NTTF's full form?

NTTF stands for Nettur Technical Training Foundation.

Can I join NTTF after 10th?

Yes, you can absolutely join NTTF after 10th!  In fact, our engineering diploma programs are designed specifically for students who have completed their 10th standard. Our 10 + 3 + 3 (10th standard + NTTF diploma + B.Tech or B.E) academic concept makes NTTF one of the best training institutes in India.This makes NTTF a great option if you’re looking for a practical, hands-on engineering education right out of school. NTTF offers a wide range of engineering diploma programs, from Computer Engineering & IT Infrastructure to Mechatronics, Manufacturing and Electrical & Electronics. This allows you to choose a specialization that aligns with your interests and career goals.

If you’re a 10th pass-out with a passion for engineering and a desire to gain practical skills, then NTTF’s diploma programs are definitely worth exploring!

What is an NTTF Diploma?

An NTTF Diploma is a specialized technical qualification offered by NTTF (Nettur Technical Training Foundation), a prestigious institution recognized for its commitment to technical education and skill development. NTTF Diplomas are widely acknowledged and accredited by various industry bodies and educational authorities, ensuring they meet high standards of quality and relevance in the field of engineering. NTTF’s programs are endorsed by organizations such as:

  • National Council for Vocational Education and Training (NCVET)
  • Ministry of Skill Development and Entrepreneurship (MSDE)
  • National Skill Development Corporation (NSDC)
  • NOCN, UK
  • NCC, UK
Who is eligible for NTTF?

Eligibility criteria for NTTF programs vary slightly depending on the specific course and program level. Generally, the following criteria apply:

  • Engineering Diploma Programs: Candidates who have completed their 10th standard (SSLC or equivalent), 12th standard or ITI are eligible to apply for NTTF’s engineering diploma programs.
  • Post-Diploma Programs: Candidates who have completed B.SC or diploma programs in relevant fields are eligible to apply for NTTF’s advanced post-diploma programs.
  • Certificate Programs: Candidates who have completed their 10th standard (SSLC).
  • Postgraduate Programs: Candidates who have completed B.E or B.Tech are eligible for NTTF’s postgraduate programs.
Is the NTTF certificate valid?

Yes, NTTF certificates are widely recognized and valued in the industry. NTTF (Nettur Technical Training Foundation) is renowned for its quality technical education and skill development programs. The certificates issued by NTTF are accredited by various national and international bodies, including:

  • Recognition by NCVET (National Council of Vocational Education and Training): NTTF certificates are aligned with the National Skill Qualification Framework (NSQF), a competency-based framework outlining skill sets for various occupations. NCVET recognition signifies that NTTF programs meet the national standards for skill development.
  • National Skill Development Corporation (NSDC): NTTF is affiliated with NSDC, underscoring its commitment to skill development and industry relevance.

These accreditations validate the credibility and industry relevance of NTTF certificates, ensuring that graduates are well-prepared for successful careers in their chosen fields.

How to get admission at NTTF?

On this official NTTF website, navigate to the “Admissions” tab on the menu or to the respective program page you’d like to apply for. Here, you will find detailed information about the programs offered, eligibility criteria, and application procedure. You can fill up the form or call our toll free number 1800 103 6883. All of the NTTF programs may require candidates to appear for an entrance exam. Prepare for and appear in the entrance exam as per the schedule provided by NTTF. You can also apply in-person. you can visit the nearest NTTF campus or your preferred campus location.

What can I do after my diploma at NTTF?

After completing a diploma at NTTF (Nettur Technical Training Foundation), you have several pathways to further your career:

  • Do a Post Diploma at NTTF: NTTF offers specialized post-diploma programs that allow you to deepen your knowledge and specialize further in your field of interest. These programs are designed to enhance your expertise and open up advanced career opportunities.
  • Pursue a Career via Campus Placement: NTTF has a robust placement cell that facilitates campus placements with leading companies across various industries. Your NTTF diploma equips you with practical skills highly sought after by employers, making you a competitive candidate in the job market.
  • Pursue a B.Tech/B.E: NTTF offers a B.Tech program in collaboration with Alliance University. This program allows you to seamlessly transition from your diploma to a bachelor’s degree, further expanding your career prospects and educational qualifications.
  • Skill Enhancement Programs: NTTF provides ongoing skill development programs and certifications tailored to industry needs. These programs keep you updated with the latest advancements in technology and management practices, enhancing your skills and employability.
What are NTTF fees?

For specific NTTF fees, please visit the respective program pages on this official NTTF website. You can download the brochure and find detailed fee information tailored to each program. This will provide you with accurate details regarding tuition fees, examination fees, and other applicable charges.

What are NTTF courses and Fees?

For specific NTTF fees, please visit the respective program pages on this official NTTF website. You can download the brochure and find detailed fee information tailored to each program. This will provide you with accurate details regarding tuition fees, examination fees, and other applicable charges.

What are the NTTF courses after 12th science/commerce with fee?

NTTF offers several courses after completing 12th standard in the science stream through a lateral entry directly to the 2nd year. Some of the prominent courses include:

  • Engineering Diploma Programs: These programs cover various disciplines such as Mechanical Engineering, Electrical & Electronics Engineering, Electronics & Communication Engineering, Computer Science & Engineering, and more.
  • Integrated B.Tech Programs: NTTF collaborates with universities like Alliance University to offer integrated B.Tech programs where students can pursue a B.Tech degree after completing their diploma.
  • Skill Development Programs: Short-term courses and certifications designed to enhance technical skills in areas such as CNC Machining, Industrial Automation, CAD/CAM, and Quality Management.
Can I join NTTF after 12th?

Yes, you can join NTTF after completing your 12th standard. NTTF offers various courses that are accessible to students who have finished their 12th grade. You can join any diploma program via lateral entry, allowing you to begin directly in the second year, especially those from science backgrounds. These courses are designed to provide specialized technical education and skills that are highly relevant to industry needs.

NTTF offers a diploma or a degree?

NTTF offers diploma programs along with certificate courses, and skill development programs. NTTF also offers Postgraduate (Masters) degrees and post graduate diploma program.

What are the benefits of NTTF training?

The benefits of NTTF training include and not limited to are:

  • Industry-Relevant Curriculum: NTTF’s training programs are designed in collaboration with industry experts, ensuring they are aligned with current industry trends and requirements.
  • Hands-On Practical Training: Emphasis on practical learning through industry projects, workshops, and hands-on 65% practical training and 35% theoretical sessions prepare students to excel in real-world scenarios.
  • Placement Assistance: Strong industry connections and a dedicated placement cell with 65 years of successful placement record, facilitate excellent placement opportunities for NTTF graduates in leading companies.
  • Skill Development: Comprehensive skill development in technical and soft skills enhances employability and career prospects.
  • Global Recognition: NTTF’s certifications and diplomas are recognized globally with NOCN and NCC recognitions, opening doors to international career opportunities.
  • Continual Learning: NTTF offers opportunities for continual learning through skill enhancement programs and certifications, keeping graduates updated with emerging technologies and industry practices.
Is the NTTF certificate valid for government jobs?

Yes, NTTF certificates are recognized and respected in various sectors, including government jobs. NTTF is accredited by NCVET and national body such as National Skill Development Corporation (NSDC). These accreditations ensure that NTTF certificates meet the standards required for eligibility in government job applications and are considered valid for such opportunities.

Can NTTF students do engineering?

Yes, NTTF students can pursue engineering. NTTF diploma holders can join a B.E and B.Tech degree program. Additionally, NTTF collaborates with universities like Alliance University to offer integrated B.Tech program. This allows NTTF students to further their education and obtain a bachelor’s degree in engineering after completing their diploma, providing a seamless pathway to higher education in engineering.

Which university is NTTF under?

NTTF conducts its diploma programs independently, without being directly affiliated with a specific university. The diplomas awarded by NTTF are highly regarded and recognized by NCVET in the industry for their quality and relevance. NTTF ensures that its all programs meet national standards and are accredited by appropriate bodies. This ensures that NTTF diploma holders are well-prepared for successful careers in their chosen fields.

How to apply for the NTTF course?

On this official NTTF website, navigate to the “Admissions” tab on the menu or to the respective program page you’d like to apply for. Here, you will find detailed information about the programs offered, eligibility criteria, and application procedure. You can fill up the form or call our toll free number 1800 103 6883. You can also visit the nearest campus or the respective campus you’d like to join. All of the NTTF programs may require candidates to appear for an entrance exam. Prepare for and appear in the entrance exam as per the schedule provided by NTTF.

What is the highest package offered in NTTF?

The highest packages offered at NTTF (Nettur Technical Training Foundation) can vary based on factors such as the specific program, industry demand, and individual student achievements.

For those seeking job opportunities within NTTF itself, positions and packages would depend on the role, qualifications, and experience relevant to the specific job openings available. For detailed information on job opportunities and potential packages, it’s advisable to regularly check NTTF’s official website or directly contact their HR department.

Which colleges can I attend after NTTF?

After completing your studies at NTTF (Nettur Technical Training Foundation), you have several pathways for further education:

  • Bachelor’s Degree Programs: NTTF diploma holders can pursue bachelor’s degrees at various colleges and universities through lateral entry, depending on your field of interest.
  • Skill Enhancement Programs: NTTF also provides skill enhancement programs and certifications that help students stay updated with industry trends and advance their careers in various technical fields.
How many courses are there in NTTF?

NTTF offers a total of 25+ programs, including:

  • 7 Diploma programs
  • 4 Post Diploma programs
  • 3 Postgraduate programs
  • 1 B.Tech program in collaboration with Alliance University
  • 4 Certificate programs
  • Learn, Earn, Grow and Succeed Programs
  • Corporate training Programs
  • Skill Development Training Programs
How are placements at NTTF campuses?

NTTF has 65+ years of track record of placements with renowned companies such as TATA, Wipro, Godrej, COTMAC, Philips, TVS, and many others. For specific details on placements, including companies visiting for recruitment and placement statistics, please drop an inquiry on this official NTTF website, the placement cell will reach out to you.

Are NTTF courses good/well-regarded?

Yes, NTTF (Nettur Technical Training Foundation) offers excellent courses that are highly regarded in the industry. NTTF is known for its practical training, industry-relevant curriculum, and strong placement support, making it a preferred choice for students aspiring to build successful careers in technical fields. The quality of education and the skills acquired through NTTF courses are valued by employers, enhancing job prospects for graduates.

What is the admission process at NTTF?

The admission process at NTTF is as below: 

  • Check Eligibility: Ensure you meet the eligibility criteria for the program you are interested in. NTTF offers various programs, and eligibility requirements can vary based on the specific course.
  • Apply on website: On this office NTTFl website, navigate to the admissions section or the respective program page. Here, you will find detailed information about the programs offered, eligibility criteria, and application procedure.
  • Fill out Application Form: Complete the online application form available on the website menu under the “Admissions” tab. Provide accurate information and upload necessary documents as specified, such as educational certificates, photo ID, etc.
  • Entrance Exam: All of the NTTF programs require candidates to appear for an entrance exam. Prepare for and appear in the entrance exam as per the schedule provided by NTTF.
  • Selection Process: After reviewing applications and entrance exam results (if applicable), NTTF will shortlist candidates for further rounds, which may include interviews or counseling sessions.
  • Admission Confirmation: Upon successful completion of the selection process, NTTF will notify you of your admission status. If selected, follow the instructions provided to confirm your admission by paying the required fees within the stipulated time frame.
  • Joining NTTF: Once admission is confirmed, attend the orientation program and commence your academic journey at NTTF.
